    "description": "<p><strong>Chapel of Christ the Redeemer Chinese Congregation</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Address:</strong></p>\n<p>2 Tampines Ave 3 Singapore 529706 (Inside St. Hilda’s Secondary School)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Tel: &nbsp;</strong>(65) 6782 9266</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Company Profile:</strong></p>\n<p>CCR Chinse Congregation was dedicated on 30 July 1989 by the Most Revd Dr. Moses Tay. In the beginning stage, it was run by the English Congregation. In November 1989, Revd Low Jee King was appointed to lead the Chinese ministry. In August 2004, we started the youth service. Over the years, Revd Eric Yong, Revd Dickson Chiu, Revd David Wong and Revd Looi Choo Huat have pastored our Congregation. Revd Lim Kek Wah is our present Pastor. Our Congregation is operated in the cell group model. Our worship service is a combination of the traditional Anglican worship style with contemporary praise and worship songs.</p>",
